Ok.
Regarding return from here, its not possible as its lambda function and is expected to traverse till the end. If return is put here it gives error - "control reaches end of non-void function [-Werror=return-type]"
One option is to catch exception as:
try
{
    std::for_each(.....
      if (condition)
      { throw true }
    );
}
catch()
{
    return true;
}
or any other way?

As per dump code owner, a valid dump is said to be available if following conditions are met for the dump entry path - Offloaded == false and Status == Completed.
Say for 
"/xyz/openbmc_project/dump/bmc/entry/1" : {
...
    "xyz.openbmc_project.Dump.Entry" : {
        "Offloaded" : {
             "type" : "b",
             "data" : false
         },
         ....
    "xyz.openbmc_project.Common.Progress" : {
        "Status" : {
            "type" : "s",
            "data" : "xyz.openbmc_project.Common.Progress.OperationStatus.Completed"
         },
         ....
...
}

I'm worried the dbus calls when checking the dump status might throw an exception, and if you don't catch them here it would abort  creating the PEL.  So I think what you had before was fine, where you would just do:

catch (const std::exception& e)
{
}

